FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The $13.506 million increase from FY 2026 to FY 2027 is due to the development of Increment 1, a comprehensive software
and firmware effort projected to last a year and a half, which is required for the successful integration of the new digital coupler in
Increment 2.
                                                                                   Accomplishments/Planned Programs Subtotals                8.423      19.709         33.215$$, $$$$, $$The Service Acquisition Executive (SAE) designated the AHFRM program a Middle Tier of Acquisition (MTA) Rapid Prototyping effort on 4 Sep 2018. To date, the
program completed a competitive rapid prototyping effort and awarded the AN/ARC-260 HF radio development contract to BAE Systems in Dec 2021. The AHFRM
program transitioned to a Major Capability Acquisition (MCA) Acquisition Category III (ACAT III) program in April 2024 to finish development and testing prior to fielding
and in addition to antenna coupler spiral development.

The Milestone Decision Authority for the program is the Combat Avionics Division Senior Material Leader-AFLCMC/ESC. Program management for the AHFRM
program is located at Warner Robins Air Force Base (AFB), Georgia. The Air Force Life Cycle Management Center - Combat Avionics Division (AFLCMC/ESC) provides
contracting, legal, comptroller, programmatic, engineering, test, and logistics support.

