Remarks$$, $$Next-Generation Overhead Persistent Infrared (Next-Gen OPIR) Polar consists of two satellites. The Next-Gen OPIR Space program was designated a Middle Tier
Acquisition (MTA) Rapid Prototype effort under Section 804 of the 2016 National Defense Authorization Act (NDAA). The Next-Gen OPIR Polar (NGP) program was re-

 designated as an Acquisition Category (ACAT)-1B Major Capability Acquisition program in Nov 2023. The first Polar satellite is required in FY 2028. The program office
 awarded a sole source contract under the authority of a Justification & Authorization document. The NGP Phase 0 was awarded in FY 2018, consisting of requirements
 development, and culminated in a March 2020 System Requirements Review (SRR). Phase 1 was awarded May 2020, encompassing requirements review, design,
 development, critical path flight hardware procurement, and risk reduction efforts leading to a System Critical Design Review (CDR) no later than FY 2024 for NGP
 Space Vehicle #1 and #2. Phase 2 was awarded in October 2024, encompassing manufacture, assembly, integration, test and launch of two satellites.

