C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                 FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
investment tradeoffs, concepts of operations, and procurement quantities providing analytically driven insights on DoW military
lethality and agility, Future Force Design, Airbase Defense, Missile Defense, Space Force structure, nuclear modernization, agile
combat support, etc informing essentially every major DAF weapon platform modernization/development investment decision
made by the SecAF, CSO and CSAF. STORM is also used by industry and coalition partners (South Korea, Turkey, United
Kingdom, Taiwan). SAF/SA executes STORM development activities and capabilities identified and prioritized by an OSW led
Joint governance structure.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continue efforts to enhance targetable space satellites from air/land/sea platforms required for FY26 SecAF/CSO space force
structure investments decisions. Leverage 2025 Integrated Air and Missile Defense Study to address MS&A gaps to support
Golden Dome / Homeland Defense analytics across the Joint services. Develop STORM's high-altitude nuclear detonation effects
models based on 2025 High-altitude Electro Magnetic Pulse effects study. Continue to develop STORM capabilities based Joint
governance structure: 1) develop over the horizon radar models Golden Dome analysis, 2) enhance space domain Air Moving
Target Indicator (AMTI) capabilities for Long-range Kill Chains, 3) containerize STORM software for deployment on cloud High
Performance Computers.
FY 2027 Plans:
FY27 PDM III would allow enhanced resolution to the STORM simulation environment to include containerization of the model
on platforms such as Morpheus and the High-Performance Computing Modernization program. Top-level model enhancements
include state-of-the-art campaign level representation of platforms, capabilities, and land formations that conduct theater-wide
combat operations in Golden Dome/homeland defense and overseas scenarios that are fully integrated with space operations.
Additionally, long-range air-to-air, ISR, and expeditionary warfare enhancements have been scoped across the Joint STORM
user community when funding is available. Additional improvements include nuclear, cyber, logistics, sea (both above and below
surface), electromagnetic spectrum, and air operations with theater-level command and control. Develop Overhead Persistent
Infrared (OPIR) capabilities for surface-to-surface missile launch detection. Enhance satellite sensor field of view, position,
coverage, and other sensor phenomena impacted by orbital mechanics. Integrate Navy's autonomous unmanned naval asset
models logistics supply chains analysis.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase due to OSW FY27 activities and inflation factor. FY27 funding increase leverages artificial intelligence, autonomy and
other new techniques to refine and modernize the STORM campaign model to add new functionality and integration of multi-
domain warfare.
